## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="0028d-138"><xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.HttpResponseMessageProperty.SuppressPreamble%2A>プロパティには、ユーザーにコンテンツを書き込むことができるように、<xref:System.Web.HttpResponseBase.OutputStream%2A>から、WCF 操作の本体の内部。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0028d-138">The <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.HttpResponseMessageProperty.SuppressPreamble%2A> property enables users to write content into the <xref:System.Web.HttpResponseBase.OutputStream%2A> from within a WCF operation body.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0028d-139">これは、web ホストのシナリオにのみ反映されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0028d-139">This takes effect only on webhosted scenarios.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0028d-140"><xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.HttpResponseMessageProperty.SuppressPreamble%2A>プロパティは`false`既定。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0028d-140">The <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.HttpResponseMessageProperty.SuppressPreamble%2A> property is `false` by default.</span></span>  
  
> [!WARNING]
>  <span data-ttu-id="0028d-141">場合、<xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.HttpResponseMessageProperty.SuppressPreamble%2A>プロパティに設定されて`true`WCF では実行できなくするため、応答で、ヘッダー、コンテンツの種類、状態コードを設定する必要があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0028d-141">If the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.HttpResponseMessageProperty.SuppressPreamble%2A> property is set to `true`, you must set the headers, content-type, status code on the response because WCF will no longer do it.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0028d-142">次のコードでは、これを行う方法の例を示します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0028d-142">The following code shows an example of how to do this.</span></span>  
  
```  
public class Service1 : IService1  
{  
   public void GetData()  
   {  
      HttpContext hc = HttpContext.Current;  
      string str = @"<?xml version=""1.0"" encoding=""utf-8"" ?>";  
      byte[] buffer = new byte[str.Length];  
      buffer = ASCIIEncoding.UTF8.GetBytes(str);  
  
      // enable the property  
      HttpResponseMessageProperty responseProperty = new HttpResponseMessageProperty();  
      responseProperty.SuppressPreamble = true;  
      OperationContext.Current.OutgoingMessageProperties[HttpResponseMessageProperty.Name] = responseProperty;  
  
      // set the response   
      hc.Response.StatusCode = 200;  
      hc.Response.ContentType = "text/xml; charset=utf-8";  
      hc.Response.ClearContent();  
      hc.Response.Flush();  
  
      hc.Response.OutputStream.Write(buffer, 0, buffer.Length);  
     hc.Response.Flush();  
   }  
}  
```
